Bernice Mbugua @BerniceMuhindi A flamboyant businessman Kevin Obia was yesterday charged with threatening to kill a security guard on March 16. He was allegedly armed with a pistol without a lawful reason and threatened to kill Yohana Imbwaka at Vue Claire Place in Kileleshwa area. He was also charged with being disorderly while carrying a firearm. Obia was arrested on Monday after a CCTV file went viral showing him brandishing the gun at the guard. Police have confiscated the gun. Principal Magistrate Peter Ooko released him on a cash bail of Sh500,000 or a bond of Sh1 million. The case will be mentioned on April 4 and heard on April 30.